==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Devoid
<hw>De*void"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>devoiden</ets> to leave, OF. <ets>desvuidier</ets>,
<ets>desvoidier</ets>, to empty out. See <er>Void</er>.]</ety> <def>To
empty out; to remove.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Devoid</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Devoid
<hw>De*void"</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Devoid</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Void; empty; vacant.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Destitute; not in possession; -- with <xex>of</xex>;
<as>as, <ex>devoid</ex> of sense; <ex>devoid</ex> of pity or of
pride.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Devoir</ent>⟦br⟧
